fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=359.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> +BS items</span><hr size=1> Does anyone know if they actually work or not. I was talking to a level 50 skald today and she told me that having items raise your BS from 46 to 50 wont make your DD's do any more damage, and that you needed to put BS up to 50 to get the most damages out of your shouts. I'm 47 now, and was wondering if anyone had ever checked into this before or not. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugisborne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/16/02 3:32:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=359.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> BS</span><hr size=1> They work just like +items for spell lines. They reduce variance until at the point when spec&gt;target level there is no variance. Thus, at 50 BS there is no variance on your DD's in RvR. Anything more is wasted for this purpose.<br>
<br>
BS will also increase your damage by about .3% per point. That's the same as +charisma, but with a cap of +11 BS and it's enchantment cost (ie +1 BS=+5 cha) it's huge waste of space.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maximumstorage>MaximumStorage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/25/02 1:39:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=359.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Really?</span><hr size=1> +BS really gives the +% dmg on dds? is there any logs for this? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
